Vice President Mike Pence spoke at Cajun Industries in Baton Rouge, Louisiana, where he discussed President Trump's recent trip abroad, including his meeting with Pope Francis and his commitment to NATO. Pence also addressed the recent terrorist attack in Manchester, expressing solidarity with the people of the United Kingdom. He praised Trump's leadership and outlined the administration's plans, including balancing the federal budget, increasing defense spending, strengthening border security, and repealing and replacing Obamacare. Pence called on Louisiana's congressional delegation to support these initiatives and emphasized the importance of prayer for the country's well-being.